"v. 玷污，污染 【英】 v.玷污，污染 (to make soiled or tarnished；defile) 【例】 sully sb's reputation(玷污名声 ) v. 玷污; 污染(使失去光辉或名声) 【记】读: 三梨－一口吃了三个鸭梨, 满身都是梨汤－玷污 【记】源自soil 弄脏；音：沙粒，弄脏衣服 sully (v.)  1590s, probably from Middle French souiller ""to soil,"" also figurative, from Old French soillier ""make dirty"" (see soil (v.)). Related: Sullied (1570s); sullying."
